# Snips

[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/nickjj/docker-symfony-demo.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/nickjj/docker-symfony-demo)

Snips is a super high quality copy-paste manager for macOS.

It was designed to be easy to use and to stay out of your way as much as
possible, so you can stay productive. It was built using the amazing Electron
project.

## Features

* A simple, intuitive interface that stays out of your way
* Search for previous copies that you have made
* Snips lives completely in your menu bar
* Copy and paste from your favorites with simple commands
* Store an unlimited amount of clippings, and easily access them from your menu bar
* A clean and simple settings page to customize Snips to work for you
* The ability to automatically launch on startup

## Installation

Snips currently supports macOS only. Download the latest release from the
[releases page](https://github.com/silentworks/snips/releases) and drag the application into your Applications folder.

